<subSubSection id="4BD86546753AFFC195CF33FF8F6FFB04" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="037D36CD753AFFC195CF33FF8F6FFB04" blockId="5.[136,1452,1165,1803]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC195CF33FF8D0BFB4C" bold="true" box="[189,318,1165,1191]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The specific epithet refers to the Subbaetic area, a region located in the south-eastern part of Córdoba province, in the geographic centre of 
<collectingRegion id="C106F82F753AFFC1974933C38E98FB20" box="[571,685,1201,1227]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Andalusia</collectingRegion>
(southern 
<collectingCountry id="7BD5765D753AFFC1965833C38F5AFB27" box="[810,879,1201,1228]" name="Spain" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Spain</collectingCountry>
). Within this region, it lies the Sierras Subbéticas Natural Park, an area protected by the government of 
<collectingRegion id="C106F82F753AFFC1979233A78F60FB04" box="[736,853,1237,1263]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Andalusia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BD86546753AFFC195CF338B8CC0F8E0" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="037D36CD753AFFC195CF338B8D81FA48" blockId="5.[136,1452,1165,1803]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC195CF338B8DD9FAF8" bold="true" box="[189,492,1273,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="C4C24D4E753AFFC1977D33888ED2FAF8" authorityName="Blanca, Cueto &amp; J. Fuentes" authorityYear="2022" box="[527,743,1273,1299]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Linaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbaetica">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC1977D33888ED2FAF8" box="[527,743,1273,1299]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Linaria subbaetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered an endemic species from the southern Iberian Peninsula (
<figureCitation id="9BF92A48753AFFC1942D326F8D93FADC" box="[351,422,1309,1335]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1096,1118]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,190,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[170,1416,190,1072]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Linaria subbaetica: Distribution map of the localities studied." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5832697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5832697/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), growing in ephemeral therophyte pastures of calcareous mountains, in the southern part of Córdoba province (
<collectingRegion id="C106F82F753AFFC194F732338DCEFAB0" box="[389,507,1345,1371]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Andalusia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7BD5765D753AFFC1977A32338E78FAB7" box="[520,589,1345,1372]" name="Spain" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Spain</collectingCountry>
). Here it grows on poorly developed and stony soils, between 
<quantity id="C43A9B28753AFFC1906E32338999FAB0" box="[1308,1452,1345,1372]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" unit="m" value="900.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="500.0">500–1300 m</quantity>
elevation, under a xeric oceanic Mediterranean Ombroclime with a Mesomediterranean Thermotype and dry Ombrotype (
<bibRefCitation id="67534B3C753AFFC195E232FB8D9DFA48" author="Mota Poveda, J. F. &amp; Sanchez Gomez, P. &amp; Guirado Romero, J. S." box="[144,424,1417,1443]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" refId="ref6287" refString="Mota Poveda, J. F., Sanchez Gomez, P. &amp; Guirado Romero, J. S. (2011) Diversidad vegetal de las yeseras ibericas. El reto de los archipielagos edaficos para la biologia de la conservacion. ADIF-Mediterraneo Asesores Consultores, Almeria, 634 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Mota Poveda 
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC1945F32F88D50FA48" box="[301,357,1417,1443]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="037D36CD753AFFC195CF32DF892EFA2C" blockId="5.[136,1452,1165,1803]" box="[189,1307,1453,1479]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC195CF32DF8D0CFA2C" bold="true" box="[189,313,1453,1479]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Phenology</emphasis>
:—The flowering period spans March to April, and fruiting time mid-April to early May.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="037D36CD753AFFC195CF32A38DF9F9D8" blockId="5.[136,1452,1165,1803]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC195CF32A38D98FA00" bold="true" box="[189,429,1489,1515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Conservation status</emphasis>
:—The distribution area of 
<taxonomicName id="C4C24D4E753AFFC1979A32A08F8AFA00" authorityName="Blanca, Cueto &amp; J. Fuentes" authorityYear="2022" box="[744,959,1489,1515]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Linaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbaetica">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC1979A32A08F8AFA00" box="[744,959,1489,1515]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Linaria subbaetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is encompassed entirely within the Sierras Subbéticas Natural Park, which was established in 1988, so it has the protection that the Andalusian government established for natural parks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="037D36CD753AFFC195CF314F8CC0F8E0" blockId="5.[136,1452,1165,1803]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">
According to the IUCN categories (2012) and recommendations provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="67534B3C753AFFC19150314F888EF9BC" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1058,1211,1597,1623]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" refId="ref5914" refString="IUCN (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 13. Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 113 pp." type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, we suggest labelling 
<taxonomicName id="C4C24D4E753AFFC195FA31108D56F990" authorityName="Blanca, Cueto &amp; J. Fuentes" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,355,1633,1659]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Linaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbaetica">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC195FA31108D56F990" box="[136,355,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Linaria subbaetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Endangered (EN), according to the following criteria: B1ac(i,ii,iv)+B2ac(i,ii,iv). Further monitoring of the known populations is recommended for a more accurate evaluation of the conservation status of this newly described species. 
<taxonomicName id="C4C24D4E753AFFC194D331D88E46F928" authorityName="Blanca, Cueto &amp; J. Fuentes" authorityYear="2022" box="[417,627,1705,1731]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Linaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbaetica">
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC194D331D88E46F928" box="[417,627,1705,1731]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Linaria subbaetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may require conservation measures and a management plan, and therefore it should be included in the Andalusian and Spanish Red Lists of vascular plants (i.e. 
<bibRefCitation id="67534B3C753AFFC1914E31BF8919F903" author="Cabezudo, B. &amp; Talavera, S. &amp; Blanca, G. &amp; Salazar, C. &amp; Cueto, M. &amp; Valdes, B. &amp; Hernandez Bermejo, J. E. &amp; Herrera, C. M. &amp; Rodriguez Hiraldo, C. &amp; Navas, D." box="[1084,1324,1741,1768]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" refId="ref5396" refString="Cabezudo, B., Talavera, S., Blanca, G., Salazar, C., Cueto, M., Valdes, B., Hernandez Bermejo, J. E., Herrera, C. M., Rodriguez Hiraldo, C. &amp; Navas, D. (2005) Lista Roja de la Flora Vascular de Andalucia. Consejeria de Medio Ambiente de la Junta de Andalucia, Sevilla, 126 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Cabezudo 
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC191C131BC88DEF90C" box="[1203,1259,1741,1767]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="67534B3C753AFFC1904431BF8CDCF8E0" author="Banares, A. &amp; Blanca, G. &amp; Guemes, J. &amp; Moreno, J. C. &amp; Ortiz, S." pageId="5" pageNumber="168" refId="ref4995" refString="Banares, A., Blanca, G., Guemes, J., Moreno, J. C. &amp; Ortiz, S. (2008, Eds.) Lista Roja 2008 de la flora vascular espanola. Direccion General de Medio Natural y Politica Forestal (Ministerio de Medio Ambiente, y Medio Rural y Marino), y Sociedad Espanola de Biologia de la Conservacion de Plantas, Madrid, 86 pp." type="book" year="2008">
Bañares 
<emphasis id="31B6EADF753AFFC190E531BC8C90F8E0" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
